{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]If you ever feel sorrow
[G]For the deeds that you have done
[F]With no hope for to[G]morrow
In the setting of the [Am]su-[F]uu-[G]un
And the oceans are [C]howlin'
[G]For things that might have been
[F]And the last good morning [G]sunrise will be
The [E]brightest you've ever [Am]seen
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
In the [F]midnight,[C]
[F]Moonlight,[C]
[G]Midnight, [E]moonlight, mid[C]-night
{end_of_chorus}


